    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline> 
                    <name type="place">Camden</name>
                    <date when="1890-06-17">P M June 17 1890</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Tom</salute>  
            </opener>
            <p>
                Nothing special or new with me—I get out an hour or two in wheel chair<ptr target="loc.03012_n1"/> most
               every day—just rec'd a splendid letter &amp; book ("Prose Poems" tree calf
               bind'g<ptr target="tex.00481_n1"/>) f'm R G Ingersoll<ptr target="n0839"/>—wonder if you w'd
               care for the enclosed autograph bit? If not throw it in the waste basket—am
               anchor'd here yet like a great helpless hulk—Send best love to the dear
               wife &amp; girl &amp; boy<ptr target="tex.00481_n2"/>—
            </p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
